cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques applied to remote sensing data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end framework that involves deep learning models, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques for semantic segmentation, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with remote sensing data, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning models for image processing, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics).
